Title: Air Disasters - Stormy Cockpit
Description: Pilots leaving Cameroon steer their plane clear of a storm, but the aircraft begins rolling to the right, and they are unable to regain control.

Title: Air Disasters - Split Decision
Description: Arrow Air Flight 1285 with 248 American soldiers on board crashes seconds after refueling in Newfoundland.

Title: Air Disasters - Dangerous Winds
Description: Three planes fall prey to deadly winds, and it is up to investigators to find out why.

Title: Air Disasters - Tree Strike Terror
Description: After a passenger jet miraculously survives a collision with trees while landing, investigators attempt to uncover why the plane was flying so low.

Title: Combat Ships - Hidden Figures
Description: Stories of historic Black struggle for equality in maritime combat; an enslaved powder boy who served during the French and Indian War; a Civil War gunner; the first African American to command a vessel with a fully integrated crew: Hugh Mulzac.

Title: Combat Ships - Record Breakers
Description: [EPG Series] A look at how technological advances over the centuries have led to bigger and faster combat ships and transformed maritime warfare.

Title: Combat Ships - Gulf War Warriors
Description: A look at key naval battles that have taken place in the Persian Gulf over the last 50 years and the warships involved, from both sides of the conflicts.

Title: Combat Ships - The Smallest Ships
Description: A look at the smallest ships of war and the major roles they've played over the centuries, including the 1776 gunboat built to stop a British invasion and the HA-19 sub.

Title: Combat Ships - Sunk
Description: New high-tech investigations uncover what sunk a World War I cruiser, a World War II submarine, a British destroyer from the Falklands War, and more.

Title: Combat Ships - Top Guns
Description: A look at how navy weapons have evolved over the centuries, from cannons to gun turrets to nuclear missiles and beyond.

Title: Combat Ships - Courageous Captains
Description: Exploring maritime heroes who left their mark on history through their bravery and skill, including Larry Chambers, Ernest Evans, and Robert Smalls.

Title: Combat Ships - River Raiders
Description: A look at riverine warfare from the Civil War to Vietnam and small but powerful combat ships.

Title: Combat Ships - Explosion!
Description: Recounting some of maritime warfare's explosions, from world wars and Vietnam to the nuclear tests at Bikini Atoll.

Title: Combat Ships - Viking Longships
Description: The story of one of the world's most effective war machines: the Viking longship, seeing how its design evolved from swift war canoe to versatile and feared ship that would change the course of history.

Title: Combat Ships - Wooden Warships
Description: A look at the most famous wooden warships over the course of 500 years.

Title: Combat Ships - Destroyers and Cruisers
Description: The ships that made mighty empires, from the lone wolves that patrolled the high seas for imperial Britain to the USS Laffey's heroic WWII battle against kamikazes at Okinawa.

Title: Air Warriors - Drones
Description: The rapid evolution of drones and how they're changing the future of aviation.

Title: Air Warriors - F-22 Raptor
Description: The inside story of the ultimate stealth fighter, the F-22 Raptor, and its predecessors.

Title: Air Warriors - F-100 Super Sabre
Description: The North American F-100 Super Saber, also known as the Hun, becomes a supersonic powerhouse after initial difficulties; it was used primarily in the Vietnam War.

Title: Air Warriors - Black Hawk
Description: The 35-year history of the UH-60 Black Hawk.

Title: Air Warriors - Top Choppers
Description: The world's most versatile and powerful helicopters, including the Huey that served as a rescue helicopter in Vietnam, and the Apache attack helicopter.

Title: Air Warriors - Galaxy
Description: An inside look at the U.S. Air Force's largest aircraft, the C-5 Galaxy; its most dramatic combat and peacetime missions over the last 50 years.

Title: Air Warriors - Top Dogfighters
Description: Stories of fighter aircraft and deadly combat, including dogfights with the P-38 Lightning and Messerschmitts over Nazi Germany, told through rarely seen battle footage and first-hand accounts.

Title: Air Warriors - B-29 Superfortress
Description: The story of the world's first nuclear bomber, the B-29, and its explosive impact on aerial warfare.

Title: Air Warriors - Zero
Description: An inside look at Japan's A6M Zero, the most feared fighter at the start of World War II.

Title: Air Warriors - C-17
Description: The inside story of the massive military transport aircraft, the C-17.

Title: Air Warriors - U-2 Dragon Lady
Description: The history and evolution of America's most legendary spy plane.

Title: Air Warriors - F-16
Description: The history of the F-16 Fighting Falcon and how it became the U.S. Air Force's most versatile plane.

Title: Aerial America - Mississippi

Title: Aerial America - Southern California
Description: A soaring tour over Southern California explores the stunning beaches, vast deserts, sprawling city and unique culture.

Title: Aerial America - Man-Made Marvels

Title: How Did They Build That? - Towers & Roofs

Description: Seasoned warrior Sarah Connor joins forces with a hybrid cyborg human and the T-800 model to protect a young woman from the Rev-9 -- a newly modified and seemingly indestructible liquid Terminator from the future.

Title: Virtuosity (1995)
Description: An ex-cop doing prison time chases a virtual-reality killer from the program onto the Los Angeles streets.

Title: Mona Lisa and the Blood Moon (2021)
Description: When a struggling single mother befriends a mysterious woman who has supernatural powers, she sees a lucrative opportunity to make some fast cash. However, their crime spree soon draws unwanted attention as the cops start to close in.
